This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it presents a method for conditional generation using Generative Adversarial Networks. Additionally, the paper involves the use of a multi-class classifier, which suggests that it may also be relevant to the sub-categories of cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of backpropagation and neural networks in the paper also suggests that it may be relevant to the sub-categories of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.MM (Multimedia).
